author: aoles
message:
Access vehicle restriction values in hgv storage as bytes rather than shorts

This addresses a possible memory alignment issue caused by the fact that hgv storage entries are 11 bytes long. As this lenght is not a multiple of 2 it can happen that the two bytes constituting a short value get distributed over two different byte array segments. However, unlike the byte-reading/writing methods the methods to directly access shorts do not allow them to be split between segments.

author: aoles
message:
fix: re-introduce edge metrics cache in matrix path extractor

Matrix path extractor uses a hashmap-based cache to keep track of encountered edges. This is a performance improvement in order to avoid re-computing metrics for edges which have been previously visited. The original solution has been removed in cbecd7d1fa8022e61ae3a0495ed2437550cc543e because it had a flaw of storing the cache entries under non-unique keys computed as sum of edge id and adjacent node id. The caching is reintroduced with a fix of using unique edge keys.

author: MichaelsJP
message:
build(spring-boot): remove fork setting

The fork setting set to false mixes up run paths but allows for local debug session. When set to true it disables the ability for a local debug session but has the expected run paths. To have local debug sessions one can use  -Dspring-boot.run.fork=false to disable forking when needed. This is only possible when the fork settings is not set at all in the pom.

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
refactor(Performance): replace concatenation in StringBuilder.append()

Inspection description:
    Reports String concatenation used as the argument to StringBuffer.append(),
    StringBuilder.append() or Appendable.append().
    Such calls may profitably be turned into chained append calls on the existing
    StringBuffer/Builder/Appendable saving the cost of an extra StringBuffer/Builder allocation.
    This inspection ignores compile-time evaluated String concatenations,
    in which case the conversion would only worsen performance.

    Example:
      void bar(StringBuilder builder, String name) {
        builder.append("Hello," + name);    //warning
        builder.append("Hello," + "world"); //no warning
      }

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
style(Java14): replace switch with new switch types

replaces normal switch with enhanced switch statements or expressions.

Note: we use a redundant default case where the
default case was the same as one of the normal cases.
This is to avoid a Language Level change to 17 (Preview),
which is only available with the --enable-preview compile
command and would require a more complex java setup.

example:
new switch expression requiring the pattern matching
    case Instruction.CONTINUE_ON_STREET, default -> InstructionType.CONTINUE;

redundant default:
    case Instruction.CONTINUE_ON_STREET -> InstructionType.CONTINUE;
    default -> InstructionType.CONTINUE;

This could be avoided if the default case actually does
something different or the duplicate normal case removed.

As this touches implementation details, it is skipped for now.

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
Enable logging in AppConfig.java

AppConfig gets called first during initializing the logger itself.
It was therefore not possible to load the default configuration from DEFAULT_LOGGING.json,
add an Appender, or change the layout of the current default sysOut appender of
the root Logger.

The current solution is to adjust the log level to INFO and reverting
to previous log level afterwards.

author: koebi
message:
`sett` as default minimum wheelchair surface type

The osm wiki denotes the previous default of `cobblestone:flattened` as
not to use. All three of `sett`, `unhewn_cobblestone` and
`cobblestone:flattened` are encoded as the same value, so no changes to
the codebase are required, it is only a matter of correct documentation.

Since `sett` is way more prevalent, it will be used as the default.

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
feat(ors-config): add CORS settings

there have been CORS issues when using our map clients with local
ors instances during development due to Problems with what headers are
accepted and exposed by the backend.
With the spring-boot update and the new run configurations using spring,
setting these options properly is now possible for local instances using
`spring-boot:run` or mvn version of it.

However, the docker approach is still using catalina + tomcat where
the settings would be passed differently, so they are not respected in
a local backend running with docker.

- add addCorsMappings function to ApiConfig class
- extent ors-config-sample.json with default cors settings working with
  all origins and accepting `Authorization` headers.
- if the api settings are missing from the ors config file,
 default values are used that correspond with the entries
 in the ors-config-sample.json

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
fix(swagger): generated swagger splits for request & response

the automatic swagger.json generation was creating some duplicate entries
since the 3.0.0 update of springfox-swagger (e.g. Directions ServiceReq &
Directions ServiceRes instead of Directions Service).
In addition this created some circular dependencies which break the
API Playground as it needs all references resolved.

The issue is described here https://github.com/springfox/springfox/issues/3487#issuecomment-1134579077
and this commit contains the solution from there to prevent the split.

author: aoles
message:
Proper handling of virtual edges in RPHAST downward search

Use the edge iterator state extracted from the subgraph edge iterator for computing edge weight during RPHAST downwards search in order to be able to resolve original edge IDs in case of virtual edges. This is necessary e.g. for the HgvAccessWeighting to be able to reliably query the HGV storage.

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
fix(openapi): response content using array schema

although objects represented by a java class are returned,
the response schema was using the @ArraySchema annotation.
This resulted in

```yaml
content:
  type: array
  items:
    $ref: ResponseObject
```

instead of the correct

```yaml
content:
  $ref: ResponseObject
```

author: MichaelsJP
message:
ci(docker): Fix the docker build github workflow

Currently, the workflow doesn't seem to correctly build for arm64 platforms. This is fixed now for the nightly images and the release workflow. arm64 tends to be really slow on building graphs while being emulated on an amd64 machine. Because of this the arm64 docker tests are only executed when the PR is set to active. Additionally, the grype checks now test both amd64 and arm64 platforms correctly.

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
chore: add GitHub issue form templates

the previous issue template was outdated and people often had
trouble with the markdown format.

By using issue forms, formatting is less error prone,
information more structured and requirements more clear.
The forms can be tailored to the issue category and labels
(or even assignees) automatically applied.

Templates were added for the following categories:
- bug reports: thorough information required
- docs: issue with the GitHub pages documentation
- feature requests
- other issues: simple form for quick issues or technical
problems not fitting the bug report

The config.yml allows for external links which point to the
forum for questions and the ors-map-client repo for issues
with the map application.

Co-authored-by: Julian Psotta <22392104+MichaelsJP@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Jakob Schnell <Jakob.Schnell@heigit.org>

author: TheGreatRefrigerator
message:
style(Java8): replace Anonymous type with lambda

Note that if an anonymous class is converted into a stateless lambda,
the same lambda object can be reused by Java runtime during subsequent
invocations.
On the other hand, when an anonymous class is used, separate objects are
created every time.
Thus, applying the quick-fix can cause the semantics change in rare cases,
e.g. when anonymous class instances are used as HashMap keys.

author: aoles
message:
chore: Clean-up path metrics extractor for matrix Dijkstra

- Remove references to CH classes from the path extractor for one-to-many Dijkstra algorithm because they cannot occur anymore in the current Graph class hierarchy.
- Calculate travel time with upstream weighting used to compute the path rather than a new instance of `FastestWeighting` in order to avoid potential mismatch e.g. in speed calculator.

author: koebi
message:
fix: rename csvColumn API parameter variable

Swagger seems to generate API parameters from getter and setter names.
Corresponding to the csv_column API parameter, getters and setters are
called getCsvColumn and setCsvColumn. This generates an API parameter
called csvColumn, that isn't there.

Renaming the variable "links" the variable and getters/setters, and the
csvColumn parameter vanishes.

message:
Correctly initialize EdgeExplorer

As stated in the graphhopper documentation, only one instance of EdgeExplorer
should ever be created. This instance is then transferred to the
CentralityAlgorithm, since it is a central part of its workings.

The EdgeExplorer used is set up to only accept outgoing edges valid for
the flagEncoder derived from the given profile.

Informing the user about a invalid excludeNode would require a
significant overhead in the calculation of nodes in the bounding box.
It could not inform the user about removing nodes he doesn't want to
remove. This has to be handled correctly by the user and is not handled
by the centrality endpoint.

message:
Explicitly create directed graph

As noted by graphhopper, edge(a, b, dist, bothDirections) is
deprecated and edge().setDistance().setFlags() is used instead.

As the used flagEncoder does not store different speeds for reverse
edges, instead of using backwards edges, use forward edges with reversed
base nodes.

author: koebi
message:
rewrite excludeNodes param Test to be graph-agnostic

Currently, we assume some node IDs to correspond to the Theodor-Heuss-Brücke in Heidelberg. Node IDs are not fixed or derived deterministically from the OSM, so updates or re-building of graphs may break this. This commit ensures that the test won't fail in this case.

log4j 2.17.1 has some security vulnerabilities. Most are fixed in 2.19.0. author: koebi
message:
build(tests): move apitests to test phase

We're using spring-boot mechanism to run apitests with the correct context.
We're not running them against the packaged jar or war file, so from the maven
pov they aren't integration tests.
This also enables us to run them with `mvn package`, using the `-Papitests` parameter.

author: koebi
message:
build: add build_graph.yml workflow

The workflow can only be run on workflow_dispatch from the GitHub UI
by ors team members.

Inputs are:
- `osm_file_url`: Download URL to the OSM pbf file (best use geofabrik)
- `environment`: GitHub environment to use
- `config_in_war`: whether the war file should include the config

Check how to create an environment on:
https://heigit.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/openrouteservice/pages/129695876/Graph+Builder+Usage

Outputs graphs, logs, elevation_cache, PBF, war and config to the
`<gh_runner_ors_repo_dir>/envs/ENV_NAME` folder on the server the GitHub runner is on.

Detailed changes in https://github.com/GIScience/openrouteservice/pull/1468

Co-authored-by: Amandus Butzer <amandus.butzer@heigit.org>

feat(ApiConfig): add environment variables for graph building

the following env vars are now available for configuring paths:
- 'GRAPHS_FOLDER': overrides 'ors.services.routing.profiles.default_params.graphs_root_path' config value
- 'ELEVATION_CACHE_FOLDER': overrides 'ors.services.routing.profiles.default_params.elevation_cache_path' config value
- 'PBF_FILE_PATH': overrides the first array entry of 'ors.services.routing.sources' config value
- 'LOGS_FOLDER': overrides 'ors.logging.location' config value

message:
fix(GH): Handling of OSM ways with invalid node refs

In cases where an OSM way had a) multiple segments handled as separate edges with b) at least one segment with at least one pillar node and c) another separate segment that is processed later with the first pillar node being invalid, graph building would stop with an exception.

author: aoles
message:
perf(isochrones): Increase edge splitting threshold

Setting the threshold to a low value slows down isochrone generation because of the increased amount of points which need to be processed when calculating the geometry. Initial benchmarks have revealed that increasing the current threshold of 20m 10-fold yields acceptable results while drastically improving performance.

message:
refactor: remove wrong instanceof checks/casts for RoutingCHGraph

chGraph always is of type RoutingCHGraph, which makes this instance of
check obsolete. QueryGraph is not a subtype of QueryRoutingCHGraph so
this cast is wrong. RoutingCHGraph already has a getEdges() method so
it is just saved in the instance.

- reorder statements for readability

message:
accept single value in `radiuses`-parameter

The `radiuses`-parameter had to have the same length as the coordinates
array. Now, a single value or an array of length 1 will be accepted and
applied to all specified waypoints.

Note, that this is a backwards-incompatible API change.
Fixes #923

fix: Fix issue #1255 bump springfox-swagger2 to 3.0.0.

This fix replaces the vulnerable version 2.9.2 with the latest 3.0.0. version. RelativePathProvider is replaced by the DefaultPathProvider making the override for getApplicationBasePath redundant, as it handles it itself now.

The following vulnerabilities are fixed with an upgrade:
- https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JAVA-COMGOOGLEGUAVA-1015415
- https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JAVA-COMGOOGLEGUAVA-32236
